caption: Thank you very much to the server for perfectly adjusting to my needs. He is very welcoming, smiling at me from start to finish. He certainly made this place well known to all. The food and coffee were all delicious and very cheap. I really recommend this coffee shop to everyone.
excellent
A very cute spot and an incredible latte! Can’t wait to come by and try the special drinks
The coffee is great !!! The service is great !!! The food is okay.It's a very nice little place, the coffee is especially good.
Best coffee around and amazing staff!

For several years now, we have been visiting this place and we don't need to miss this place anymore! They've got more than coffee here. For breakfast, lunch and dinner, Aromas has a fantastic menu of daily specials. We ate several times at this spot during our time here, and all was excellent. A tour is worth it!
Really great coffee. I would rate this as one of the best espresso shop I have visited.  A nice, small breakfast to start the day. Nearly feels like home. Recommended!!
So great. Unbeatable prices,  great staff, warm, spacious, and a great place to work. All you can ask for. Highly appreciated!!!

The most high-grade coffee shop. It's one of the best places here to let you know. The atmosphere is fantastic with amazing, lovely staff. They have some great coffee here. It was all addictive. They also have books to read. Highly recommended!

I fell in love with this cute coffee shop and its staff the first time I popped in. They have great coffee and I was happy for that. We enjoy going there whenever possible. It's clean, well run, and the owners are genuinely nice people!
This shop serves the best chocolate, coffee, espresso, and cappuccino that you will ever satisfy in! The atmosphere is pleasant and cheerful.

The deconstructed latte IS MY JAM. When I had first heard about it I thought you know it's a little gimmicky (if you watch Top Chef, it seems the whole deconstruction thing was a phase that passed). And yet, deep in my sole I wanted it so badly. And when I finally, FINALLY had...I realized how well it works.  You got to taste and appreciate the espresso, which was beautiful, that I had to drink a little with the milk, but the separation of it made me appreciate the creaminess and sweetness of the milk so that when I finished the deconstructed aspects and moved on to the latte, I could drink it without sugar, and I have never been one to be able to take my latte without sugar. It was lovely!  The decor and atmosphere in the space is beautiful. It shows meticulous concern, love of coffee, and good use of space/tables for people who are there to work/catch up. It's very warm and makes me happy!  I've since met the owner who is all-around goodness - sweet, humble, and clearly cares about coffee. Everyone else who I've come across who works there have also exuded similar vibes which is so rare and so great.  I have also tried the nitro with milk - only my second time having nitro, and it was lovely as well. I have bought bags of the drip coffee beans because it is perfect for the picky eater/coffee drinker.  Definitely my favorite place to have coffee across the US (I have tried a lot of coffee places...).
manage a team

Pretty good coffee shop! I’m not sure if they’re still doing any special menu items due to covid, but when I came here I was disappointed to find that the deconstructed latte was only available with dairy milk. I’m lactose intolerant :(  My macchiato was a little over extracted (but not bad) but my husbands cortado was great. Overall I think coffee project is a bit overhyped but still probably worth a stop if you’re in the area!

I can really say that this Coffee Shop is the best in this area because they served the most delicious coffee in the town.  The bittersweet taste of it was really my style. The aroma was so relaxing. The cakes and pastries they had were very satisfying. Especially, their brunch very delicious it is a must-try!

Very nice coffee, renowned for its carrot cake. Meals very tasty and good value. Lovely staff  and accommodating. This is the best place if the weather is bad like rainy day because when it's cold, it's nice to have coffee. I would always look for this place for they have great service and nice atmosphere.

Its atmosphere is homey, and the menu contains a variety of dishes and drinks. It is well air-conditioned, and the music played on the speakers was generally lovely. Truly a must-visit coffee shop!

Delicious coffee and amazing specialty drinks. Got the coconut supercharger (double shot over coconut water with chunks of coconut) and it was mind blowing. Delicious fresh baked good too. They have a nice outdoor seating area with tables well spaced. Highly recommend for all coffee lovers.

Super friendly and the lemon ginger scone was amazing! Very kind staff, went with my French Bulldog and sat outside. They were all around amazing. Will be back. #supportsmallbusiness

Keeping up good cheer and excellent coffee. Really dedicated to high quality customer service and high quality espresso as well (and pourovers!). They are very much into the weeds in their passion for coffee - come for a great drink, and if you want to go into the details, you can do that too.
This is the loveliest spot! Friendly baristas, bright sunlit space and delicious latte that came with a small glass of sparkling water. I'll be back :)
Fantastic cappuccino and drip. Always crowded despite the missing signage.

Coffee Project NY was one of my last destinations this past weekend, for my weekender trip or D3. I did not exactly know about them before this visit, as I searched for a coffee shop in Brooklyn on a whim, having been staying and exploring Brooklyn for the weekend. Nevertheless, I'm glad that I got to try this coffee shop than others. If anything, I'm a fellow coffee person with my own brewers (hario V60 and chemex), gooseneck kettle, and electric conical burr grinder at home. There are a good portion of coffee shops that do have the pour-over available, but some still have this automated to save their baristas time for other orders. This is understandable, but there's that factor that's lost when you start to automate these. This brings me to the point of their emphasis on coffee, and that I was happy to see them focusing on the pour-over. It might look really simple but there's more fine-print to it, especially that with the temperature, grinds, and the pour technique during the brewing process. In addition to these, the space is rather spacious and very conducive to either doing work or socializing with friends/family. I'm also glad that they mention having this location as a "playground" for baristas, as this empowers them to perfect their craft of coffee. Will definitely be coming back here, and may even take one of their classes to supplement my own craft of coffee at home!

i used to love this place and was so happy they opened a branch in brooklyn. today was the first time i visited here after a couple of months and there were a couple of disappointing changes. although the coffee was still excellent but the lemon loaf cake i ordered was definitely old and dry and NOT WORTH $4.50 for such a small piece. the last time i ordered, it was moist and lemony at least!  then what happened to the ambience? it used to be totally chilled with not too loud (and decent) background music but today they are blasting mediocre pop album that i cannot even think. maybe it all depends on who's working and i was unlucky today but i'll have to think twice about coming back again.
Very good!! Coffee delicious

The coffee is really great but the service is slow. Not a place to go if you’re on your way somewhere.  Last month, they forgot my drink. This time, it took 15 minutes to get a latte with no one in front of me...
Amazing coffee.  Cool vibe.
Great coffee shop! Coffee is delicious and there is a nice vibe! Free WiFi and about 5 small tables and 1 long table
great coffee

A really nice relaxing place. I recommend the Slow Bar so that you can enjoy a delicate pour-over. Drinks much more like a tea than a coffee, which was delightful. The barista was also very knowledgeable and friendly. We spoke at length about coffee.  Highly recommended.
Coffee was warm and not hot. They couldnt even reheat the coffee since they dont have a microwave which was weird. Very average place
Our favorite coffee shop on our visit to NY. Delicious coffee and a a beautiful shop. Fantastic service and to top it off, gluten free lemon bread! Heaven!!
Lots of seating, outlets and wifi, and good tasting coffee

I was surprised to find this spot. It is hidden in a back street, across from whole foods! Perfect spot for work and study.  Specialty coffee spot mainly, not your cheap coffee shop spot.  I tried the "deconstructed latte?" Which was a pleasant surprise: shot of espresso, shot of warm frothy milk, a late, waffle cracker, and sparkling water to clean the palad.
Great place to get some work done. Street has few pedestrians so the shop isn't loud or crowded.
Love it. Favourite drink = Nitro. Try it!
Came in here with a friend to shield from the cold and have a hot chocolate. Thank you for making it the best way possible: the perfect size for a super rich drink.
Baristas are oh so knowledgeable. Space is beautiful and the coffee is divine💗
Great service and good coffee

Wonderful coffee - I always recommend the nitro cold brew. This location has more space than the original Manhattan one, so it's great if you want to meet someone for a coffee or have a drink to stay and enjoy the coffee shop vibe.
Awesome coffee. Awesome place. Awesome staff :) thank you for a great time..

Nice low key and atmosphere. Wish the lights were a bit dimmer but anyway the coffee is great obv. They’re using the Chemex which is one step above the French press. And the tea options seem to be plentiful.
(Translated by Google) We are from Argentina and we loved coffee and attention  (Original) Somos de Argentina y nos encantó el café y la atencion
Best coffee in the United States. They are true coffee craftswomen!  One of the things we miss the most from our NYC days. We still talk about them from time to time.  Amazing staff - we love you!
My favorite coffee place in the city. Great folks, incredible coffee. Best nitro brew in town.
Oat milk cappuccino was delicious and made perfectly. The service is great here. Worth your time.
Solid cascading nitro cold brew , and they warm up the croissant for you
Coffee taken to another level.  Take the class! It's so interesting
Great place for coffee, nice and clean Brooklyn-style decoration. Happy to have options beyond bug chains.
Love this place. One of the few spots you can get actually good coffee. The owners really care about the quality and even encourage their baristas to train to compete in coffee competitions.
The lemon loaf we had here has perfect balanced taste. Milk foam is so smoothly, especially for my friend who doesn’t like bitter taste.  This is the most friendly coffee shop in the neighborhood!

Nothing special here.  Extremely overpriced and their signature offerings are nothing more than a name. As there are 2 bigger coffee shops and a Starbucks literally a block away, you won't find anything out of the ordinary here. The one pro is as this is a hard to spot place, it makes for a quaint spot to relax at.
Fantastic 3rd wave coffee with hard to find techniques for making coffee (ex: iced pour over), and rotating roasters. Also a chill place to just hang out with wifi and affogatos.
A nice place for coffee time!
We’re in NYC on vacation. Found this nice place while walking through Brooklyn and craving for coffee. Very nice, very tasty! Greetings from Germany! Thank you
Great vibe and friendly service!
Very cute! Very fancy! Nice space and not over crowded (yet).
Quaint place
I love everything about this place. Great coffee and space, and one of the friendliest places in the hood! Don’t ever change!

Wow. The best coffee I've had in some time. The steampunk brew was fantastic. A Bolivian coffee, super clear - no sediment at all, good body, winey. The deconstructed latte is also a must. They source their coffee from fantastic roasters , including Denmark's coffee collective. Super happy with this find. Will be back often. 10/10
Service was beyond expectation and the food very good.
Great atmosphere and coffee!

Was impressed with the coffee and very impressed with the service. There was a small mixup with the pastry that was ordered, staff misheard and brought something slightly different. They replaced without extra charge. Small thing and something that should be done but we take for granted common sense and excellent service...therefore, their excellent service was appreciated and was the cherry on top of the presentation and quality of the items that were ordered.

I LOVE this coffee shop SOOO MUCH! Delicious coffee, with many varied ways of delivery - cold brew to affogatos you name it. They also have really good non caffeinated options, and plenty of sweet and savory snacks too. The decor is sooooo good, minimal but bright and a great escape from the grey surroundings in that area. Their table ware is so well curated, using their tiny spoons and lovely glass tea kettles is a joy. You guys are doing a really great job keep it up!!

Incredible coffee, good seating, helpful baristas, but a tad spendy. Some of their unusual offerings (nitro flights or deconstructed lattes?) are a tasty way to try something new and learn a bit more about the drinks.  Seating was also surprisingly abundant when I stopped in on a Saturday afternoon.  Only downside: those interesting unusual drinks will also cost you too much.
The Batista's were super friendly, the space is open, and the coffee was great!

Great coffee shop.   Loving the development on this strip of Rockwell Pl.   This is a great spot to sit a chill during the afternoons with friends or alone.   Space has a decent sitting area.  They have restrooms.  Staff is really friendly and engaging.   It's a block from BAM and Fulton Mall.   Try this spot over Hungry Ghost around the corner.  Like Hungry Ghost but better coffee and cooler atmosphere. Coffee is good.   And they offer a decent amount of snack/lunch options.   Prices are average for coffee shops in area.    Great spot to have in neighborhood.    Looking forward to Future visits.
One of my favorite place for specialty coffee in NYC! Great beans, amazing brew skills, knowledgeable staff, comfy atmosphere.. you NEED to try!
This coffee shop in Brooklyn is fabulous! Great staff, coffee, atmosphere!! Get there!!
Top notch coffee! Really love the croissant sandwiches too - the egg salad is 10/10!

Great coffee place near Atlantic Barclays center. They have a lot of space, so great place to sit and eat. They have a lot of food options. I had the chai latte with oat milk and it was delicious. There pastries are also tasty. I had the vegan banana bread which was good.

The staff is so nice here! Told them it was my first time visiting along with my sister mom and son, they were very nice and guided us threw the various selections on their menu. When you go get their special project coffee!
Lovely baristas, cute space, great coffee, yummy pastries 👍🏼
Dog friendly! Cute place, not so easy to find if you don't know it is there. Coffee is good. Service was great. WiFi is available and some tables have no laptop signs.
Great latte, friendly staff
Everything is delish !!!!! Great coffee, from an Aussie 💚😉
Fantastic coffee and espresso, tons of seating, WiFi, good vibes, friendly staff
They use the best non dairy mylk for their delicious coffee blend: OATLEY BARISTA ❤️❤️❤️
While no cold brew in the world is worth $4.75, this is probably the closest you're likely to find to justifying that price.
Best Coffee Ever!
Awesome espresso. Cool vibe.

We were so excited when the Brooklyn location opened - their Manhattan location is one of the few places I ever would have commuted to from Brooklyn just for coffee.  It's hard to say what's better between the people who work here and the drinks they make. Both are amazing, highly recommended!
Great coffee! Lovely baristas, plus a beautiful space. Also they have a super cool, high tech drip machine. You gotta see it!
